<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Project on Treebeard Creations</title><link>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/tags/project/</link><description>Recent content in Project on Treebeard Creations</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 17 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://treebeardcreations.github.io/tags/project/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Compost Toilets</title><link>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/compostloo/</link><pubDate>Tue, 17 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/compostloo/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Staircase</title><link>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/staircase/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/staircase/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="finally-upgrading-the-staircase-at-boggart-hall"&gt;Finally upgrading the staircase at Boggart Hall&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id="a-project-for-my-friend-grace"&gt;A project for my friend Grace.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I met Grace many years ago during what I now call a recharge part of my life, following stressful times and a reset a friend recommended I try a website called &lt;a href="http://www.thepoosh.org/"&gt;the poosh dot org&lt;/a&gt;, which at the time, (it seems to have shut down now), offered a similar service to woofing (working on organic farms) so you would offer your service in exchange for bed and board, or whatever arrangement suits all parties. So I ended up in Todmorden on a concrete slab cutting huge larch timber frames in exchange for wonderful cakes and buiscuits and a warm dry space to sleep. I intended to stay for a couple of months, get the frame up, meet Barbara Jones of &lt;a href="https://strawworks.co.uk/"&gt;Straworks&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://schoolofnaturalbuilding.co.uk/"&gt;School of Natural Building&lt;/a&gt; and learn a little about Straw Bale building. This turned out to be almost 18 months initially, staying on to help with the roof structure and a few other bits before setting off to work with Barbara Jones on her next big project, I did however continue to return throughout the following years, each time returning to help on the next room, the kitchen, batroom, office etc. always in exchange for sustanance and warmth. My time over the years with Grace allowed me to live as close as possible to money free and I can safely say that without bills and payslips, tax returns and all the other ridiculous buraucracy I felt about as stress free as I ever have as an adult. If reading this you get an opportunity to travel and meet the people you do volunteering I highly recomend it.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Vernacular Reconstruction</title><link>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/vernacular/</link><pubDate>Sat, 06 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/vernacular/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stage-1---from-local-resource-to-traditional-frame"&gt;Stage 1 - From local resource to traditional frame&lt;/h1&gt;
