&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of my favourite projects and an honour to be the Carpenter for the project. Originally concieved as a joint venture between Hill Holt architecture student Chris Myk and local community Archaologist Emily Gillott and a community volunteer project at Skylarks Nature reserve in Nottingham. Remains of various structures had been found and excavated on site and from the remains we collaborated to design what we thought could have been built on the site during Saxon times. I shall not go into too much detail on the archaology as I&amp;rsquo;m no expert, but it was interesting speaking to the archaeologists about details they&amp;rsquo;d found in old timber frames that still directly relates to the way we do things today.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Anglesey Cludgy</title><link>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/cludgy/</link><pubDate>Fri, 05 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://treebeardcreations.github.io/cludgy/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A project completed Spring 2012 for my Aunt on Anglesey.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



